Prague MDD takes us on Wednesday for the first time with the chip
On Wednesday, October 1, 2008, we write in the history of the Prague Transport Company on the date when the first passengers enter the subway, the tram and the bus with an electronic bonus in their pockets instead of a paper ticket.
This can be purchased at this moment by nearly one hundred thousand people who have the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy the 30-day, 90-day and annual bonus (this will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time load it on their chip card in the info centres and transport company stations in the Metro, Museum, Móstek, Nadraží Holesovice, Andel, Roztyly, Letnyany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
Bonuses can be purchased from yesterday on the Internet on the transport company’s pages, www.dpp.cz.
The service was used by more than four hundred people until the afternoon.
Those who start using the Internet as a form of trade can definitely start to forget the ticket sales stations in the metro stations, where they had to regularly take a round to get a normal ticket.
The bonus is purchased online, and the Opencard card is recharged in one of the 13 branches of the Municipal Library.
"In these places there is available to passengers a window with prepared staff that helps interested people with online purchases and also with the recharge of the bonus purchased on their card," said project spokesman Martin Opatrný.
Apart from the library, it will also be possible to recharge the electronic bonus on the Opencard in the vending machines located in some of the metro lobbyes.
How are these expensive machines?
They are red, they remind us of a ticketing machine and the travelers will probably have already been fixed in them at the stations of the Roztyly Metro, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Now there are five in the city but at the end of the year there would have to be eighty," Opatrný said.
The bonus is controlled by the machine instead of the driver
The use of the machine, which will start working tomorrow, is simple.
Just enter in it the Opencard chip card and the previously paid bonus will be loaded only in it.
The electronic bonds since tomorrow are valid not only in the capital but also in its surroundings.
That is, in the roundabout trains and bus lines from 300 to 499 that mainly use the inhabitants of central Bohemia.
"In the trains attached to the integrated transport of Prague, there are auditors equipped with a reading card that will help confirm the validity of the time and zone of the bonus," explained the control of the tickets, Filip Drápal of the organization Ropid, which sets the timetables for the collective transport of Prague.
Circuit buses have their reading cards mounted in the driver’s tachyllus.
Upon entering it is necessary not only to show the card to the driver but also to accompany it with the Opencard in the place intended for it on the side of the Box.
With this, the driver controls the validity of the bonus.
"If the passenger needs to verify the validity of the bonuses there is nothing easier than to ask the driver for this information," Drápal said.
Passengers who do not travel on the surrounding buses and do not remember when they finish the bonus validity can be addressed to the forwarding machines where the cards are recharged.
Here you will see information about the validity of your document on the computer screen.
